[line]

[size=3][b]FAQ[/b][/size]

[b]How do I make events occur faster or slower?[/b]
See the Presets section above, or fine-tune individual sliders in MCM.

[b]Does it conflict with the vanilla task system?[/b]
No. AlifePlus validates every entity through protection gates at every pipeline layer. Task givers, companions, active quest squads, and externally scripted squads are protected.

[b]Does it work with GAMMA?[/b]
Built and tested with GAMMA, also tested partially with Zona and EFP. Works directly with X-Ray engine callbacks without modifying base scripts.

[b]Does it work with other A-Life mods?[/b]
No known incompatibilities, including with warfare and AI addons, but will conflict behavior-wise with mods doing a lot of scripting on squads.

[b]Does it work mid-save?[/b]
Yes.

[b]Do I need offline combat enabled?[/b]
No. AlifePlus never requires or prefers online simulation. It works with all offline settings, including fully disabled. Offline combat produces fewer combat events but the system generates other events regardless, so A-Life activity continues.

[line]

[size=3][b]Known Issues[/b][/size]
Map markers are a debugging feature. They lack persistence and do not update on entity death, despawn, or level transition.

[line]

[size=3][b]Validation[/b][/size]
Multi-stage validation pipeline:
[list]
[*]luacheck, selene (static analysis)
[*]tree-sitter AST analysis, ast-grep structural patterns
[*]Contract rules (API safety, cross-file dependencies, cyclomatic complexity, coding standards)
[*]lua54 integration testing with X-Ray engine stubs
[*]gitleaks, trufflehog (secret scanning)
[/list]

